h3. Issue Summary

When trying to edit the Display Options in the Jira Issue macro, the changes are not being saved and the macro display does not change. If you first selected the single issue view and then try to change it to the table view, the macro will keep showing the single issue view or vice-versa. This issue is occurring only in the new editor.
h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Insert a Jira Issue macro to the page (or try to edit an existing one);
 # Filter to a specific issue (e.g key = PROJECT-1);
 # Click on "Insert";
 # Edit the macro;
 # Click in "Display Options";
 # Change the view from single to table (or vice-versa);
 # Click on "Insert";
 # Notice that the macro will not change its display in the page.

h3. Expected Results

The macro should change from single issue to table or vice-versa.
h3. Actual Results

The display options are not being saved and the macro does not change the view from single issue to table or vice-versa.
h3. Workaround

Re-add the macro to the page and select the desired option (single/table) directly.
